1 former team, the Milwaukee Bucks; and
2 WHEREAS, Junior Bridgeman was an important and active member of his adopted
3 hometown of Louisville and supported causes across the Commonwealth. He served as
4 chair of the University of Louisville's Board of Trustees, and was on the board of the
5 Louisville Free Public Library, West End School, the Louisville Arena Authority, the
6 Crusade for Children Foundation, and the African American Heritage Foundation; and
7 WHEREAS, Junior Bridgeman left these earthly bonds on March 11, 2025, and his
8 sudden passing left behind a community reeling from the loss of this soft-spoken man
9 who left a giant impact; and
10 WHEREAS, it is notable that Junior Bridgeman passed away while at a fundraiser
11 for the Lincoln Heritage Council of the Boy Scouts of America, where he shared a
12 personal story of not having the financial resources to participate in scouting when he
13 was a boy and encouraged attendees not to let those barriers impact the next generation of
14 potential scouts; and
15 WHEREAS, the scores of tributes and accolades to the life and legacy of Junior
16 Bridgeman can best be summed up by this statement issued by the University of
17 Louisville: "Today we lost a legend and beloved member of the Louisville basketball
18 family, Junior Bridgeman leaves an unmatched legacy and we are forever grateful for the
19 impact he’s made on our program, our university and our city. We send our deepest
20 condolences to the Bridgeman family and all who loved him."; and
21 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper that the extraordinary life and accomplishments
22 of Junior Bridgeman be publicly recognized;
23 NOW, THEREFORE,
24 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
25 Kentucky:
26 Section 1. The Senate does hereby express its most profound sympathy upon
27 the passing of Ulysses Lee "Junior" Bridgeman, recognizes his tremendous
